## Summary of the fix:

The issue was in the `@mixin max-width-container` in `styles/_mixins.scss`. The problem occurred because:

1. **Before**: The `max-width: $max-width-container;` declaration was placed after the nested `@media` rule
2. **After**: I moved the `max-width: $max-width-container;` declaration before the nested `@media` rule

This change ensures compliance with the upcoming CSS specification that Sass is adopting, where all declarations must appear before nested rules within the same block.

The fix maintains the exact same functionality while eliminating the deprecation warning. The mixin will continue to work exactly as before, but now follows the new CSS declaration ordering requirements.
